---
import Base from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<Base title="About" description="Foundations was built to give trades contractors the web presence their work already earns — with full ownership." path="/about/">
  <section>
    <div class="wrap" style="max-width:720px">
      <p class="label">About</p>
      <h1 style="margin-top:12px">Built for the trades. Owned by you.</h1>
      <p style="margin-top:24px;font-size:1.1rem">
        Foundations exists for one reason: too many great contractors build like an A and show up
        online like a C. They've got the reviews, the craftsmanship, the referrals — and a website
        that's slow, thin, or trapped on a platform they'll never own.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top:18px;color:var(--muted)">
        We come out of the remodeling world. We know what wins a homeowner's trust and what loses it.
        That's why everything we build, you own — the domain, the code, the content, all of it. No
        markup on your ad spend, no monthly hostage fees, no platform that holds your business ransom.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top:18px;color:var(--muted)">
        Just a fast, clean, conversion-built web presence that does what your reputation already
        deserves: gets you found, and gets you chosen.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top:36px">
        <a class="btn" href="/contact/">Start with a free Report Card</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
